I"Ù<p>Consonant with the premotor theory of attention, triggering an <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/saccades-and-smooth-pursuit-exapt-gaze-stabilization-reflex">eye saccade</a> results in <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/premotor-theory-of-attention-is-fundamentally-enactive">a covert movement of attention</a>. This can be observed through increased discriminative ability for the region in the immediate vicinity of a subsequent saccade target.</p>
